definitions.definition: The amount , number or rate of something, regarded as part of a total of 100; a part of a whole.
examples: A high percentage of secondary school leavers take a gap year.

definitions.definition: A share of the sales, profits, gross margin or similar.
examples: She gets a percentage for every vacuum cleaner sold.
There was no percentage in staying at home.

main_definition: The amount , number or rate of something, regarded as part of a total of 100; a part of a whole.
secondary_definitions: A share of the sales, profits, gross margin or similar.
